      "span_text": "At study entry and at the checkup visits, OME was determined according to the Maastricht Otitis Media With Effusion Study algorithm, which is based on the results of tympanometry and nonpneumatic otoscopy. Tympanograms were classified according to the algorithm of Jerger, 11 in which OME was considered to be present when tympanometry resulted in a type B or C2 tympanogram combined with otoscopic findings that suggested the presence of effusion in the middle ear (eg, glue and fluid lines or bubbles) and no signs of acute ear infection."
